4722static void merge_check_renames_reusable(struct merge_options *opt,
4723           struct merge_result *result,
4724           struct tree *merge_base,
4725           struct tree *side1,
4726           struct tree *side2)
4727{
4728  struct rename_info *renames;
4729  struct tree **merge_trees;
4730  struct merge_options_internal *opti = result->priv;
4731
4732  if (!opti)
4733    return;
4734
4735  renames = &opti->renames;
4736  merge_trees = renames->merge_trees;
4737
4738  /*
4739   * Handle case where previous merge operation did not want cache to
4740   * take effect, e.g. because rename/rename(1to1) makes it invalid.
4741   */
4742  if (!merge_trees[0]) {
4743    assert(!merge_trees[0] && !merge_trees[1] && !merge_trees[2]);
4744    renames->cached_pairs_valid_side = 0; /* neither side valid */
4745    return;
4746  }
4747
4748  /*
4749   * Handle other cases; note that merge_trees[0..2] will only
4750   * be NULL if opti is, or if all three were manually set to
4751   * NULL by e.g. rename/rename(1to1) handling.
4752   */
4753  assert(merge_trees[0] && merge_trees[1] && merge_trees[2]);
4754
4755  /* Check if we meet a condition for re-using cached_pairs */
4756  if (oideq(&merge_base->object.oid, &merge_trees[2]->object.oid) &&
4757      oideq(&side1->object.oid, &result->tree->object.oid))
4758    renames->cached_pairs_valid_side = MERGE_SIDE1;
4759  else if (oideq(&merge_base->object.oid, &merge_trees[1]->object.oid) &&
4760     oideq(&side2->object.oid, &result->tree->object.oid))
4761    renames->cached_pairs_valid_side = MERGE_SIDE2;
4762  else
4763    renames->cached_pairs_valid_side = 0; /* neither side valid */
4764}

4766/*** Function Grouping: merge_incore_*() and their internal variants ***/
4767
4768/*
4769 * Originally from merge_trees_internal(); heavily adapted, though.
4770 */
4771static void merge_ort_nonrecursive_internal(struct merge_options *opt,
4772              struct tree *merge_base,
4773              struct tree *side1,
4774              struct tree *side2,
4775              struct merge_result *result)
4776{
4777  struct object_id working_tree_oid;
4778
4779  if (opt->subtree_shift) {
4780    side2 = shift_tree_object(opt->repo, side1, side2,
4781            opt->subtree_shift);
4782    merge_base = shift_tree_object(opt->repo, side1, merge_base,
4783                 opt->subtree_shift);
4784  }
4785
4786redo:
4787  trace2_region_enter("merge", "collect_merge_info", opt->repo);
4788  if (collect_merge_info(opt, merge_base, side1, side2) != 0) {
4789    /*
4790     * TRANSLATORS: The %s arguments are: 1) tree hash of a merge
4791     * base, and 2-3) the trees for the two trees we're merging.
4792     */
4793    err(opt, _("collecting merge info failed for trees %s, %s, %s"),
4794        oid_to_hex(&merge_base->object.oid),
4795        oid_to_hex(&side1->object.oid),
4796        oid_to_hex(&side2->object.oid));
4797    result->clean = -1;
4798    return;
4799  }
4800  trace2_region_leave("merge", "collect_merge_info", opt->repo);
4801
4802  trace2_region_enter("merge", "renames", opt->repo);
4803  result->clean = detect_and_process_renames(opt, merge_base,
4804               side1, side2);
4805  trace2_region_leave("merge", "renames", opt->repo);
4806  if (opt->priv->renames.redo_after_renames == 2) {
4807    trace2_region_enter("merge", "reset_maps", opt->repo);
4808    clear_or_reinit_internal_opts(opt->priv, 1);
4809    trace2_region_leave("merge", "reset_maps", opt->repo);
4810    goto redo;
4811  }
4812
4813  trace2_region_enter("merge", "process_entries", opt->repo);
4814  process_entries(opt, &working_tree_oid);
4815  trace2_region_leave("merge", "process_entries", opt->repo);
4816
4817  /* Set return values */
4818  result->path_messages = &opt->priv->conflicts;
4819
4820  result->tree = parse_tree_indirect(&working_tree_oid);
4821  /* existence of conflicted entries implies unclean */
4822  result->clean &= strmap_empty(&opt->priv->conflicted);
4823  if (!opt->priv->call_depth) {
4824    result->priv = opt->priv;
4825    result->_properly_initialized = RESULT_INITIALIZED;
4826    opt->priv = NULL;
4827  }
4828}

4830/*
4831 * Originally from merge_recursive_internal(); somewhat adapted, though.
4832 */
4833static void merge_ort_internal(struct merge_options *opt,
4834             struct commit_list *merge_bases,
4835             struct commit *h1,
4836             struct commit *h2,
4837             struct merge_result *result)
4838{
4839  struct commit *next;
4840  struct commit *merged_merge_bases;
4841  const char *ancestor_name;
4842  struct strbuf merge_base_abbrev = STRBUF_INIT;
4843
4844  if (!merge_bases) {
4845    merge_bases = get_merge_bases(h1, h2);
4846    /* See merge-ort.h:merge_incore_recursive() declaration NOTE */
4847    merge_bases = reverse_commit_list(merge_bases);
4848  }
4849
4850  merged_merge_bases = pop_commit(&merge_bases);
4851  if (!merged_merge_bases) {
4852    /* if there is no common ancestor, use an empty tree */
4853    struct tree *tree;
4854
4855    tree = lookup_tree(opt->repo, opt->repo->hash_algo->empty_tree);
4856    merged_merge_bases = make_virtual_commit(opt->repo, tree,
4857               "ancestor");
4858    ancestor_name = "empty tree";
4859  } else if (merge_bases) {
4860    ancestor_name = "merged common ancestors";
4861  } else {
4862    strbuf_add_unique_abbrev(&merge_base_abbrev,
4863           &merged_merge_bases->object.oid,
4864           DEFAULT_ABBREV);
4865    ancestor_name = merge_base_abbrev.buf;
4866  }
4867
4868  for (next = pop_commit(&merge_bases); next;
4869       next = pop_commit(&merge_bases)) {
4870    const char *saved_b1, *saved_b2;
4871    struct commit *prev = merged_merge_bases;
4872
4873    opt->priv->call_depth++;
4874    /*
4875     * When the merge fails, the result contains files
4876     * with conflict markers. The cleanness flag is
4877     * ignored (unless indicating an error), it was never
4878     * actually used, as result of merge_trees has always
4879     * overwritten it: the committed "conflicts" were
4880     * already resolved.
4881     */
4882    saved_b1 = opt->branch1;
4883    saved_b2 = opt->branch2;
4884    opt->branch1 = "Temporary merge branch 1";
4885    opt->branch2 = "Temporary merge branch 2";
4886    merge_ort_internal(opt, NULL, prev, next, result);
4887    if (result->clean < 0)
4888      return;
4889    opt->branch1 = saved_b1;
4890    opt->branch2 = saved_b2;
4891    opt->priv->call_depth--;
4892
4893    merged_merge_bases = make_virtual_commit(opt->repo,
4894               result->tree,
4895               "merged tree");
4896    commit_list_insert(prev, &merged_merge_bases->parents);
4897    commit_list_insert(next, &merged_merge_bases->parents->next);
4898
4899    clear_or_reinit_internal_opts(opt->priv, 1);
4900  }
4901
4902  opt->ancestor = ancestor_name;
4903  merge_ort_nonrecursive_internal(opt,
4904          repo_get_commit_tree(opt->repo,
4905                   merged_merge_bases),
4906          repo_get_commit_tree(opt->repo, h1),
4907          repo_get_commit_tree(opt->repo, h2),
4908          result);
4909  strbuf_release(&merge_base_abbrev);
4910  opt->ancestor = NULL;  /* avoid accidental re-use of opt->ancestor */
4911}
4912
4913void merge_incore_nonrecursive(struct merge_options *opt,
4914             struct tree *merge_base,
4915             struct tree *side1,
4916             struct tree *side2,
4917             struct merge_result *result)
4918{
4919  trace2_region_enter("merge", "incore_nonrecursive", opt->repo);
4920
4921  trace2_region_enter("merge", "merge_start", opt->repo);
4922  assert(opt->ancestor != NULL);
4923  merge_check_renames_reusable(opt, result, merge_base, side1, side2);
4924  merge_start(opt, result);
4925  /*
4926   * Record the trees used in this merge, so if there's a next merge in
4927   * a cherry-pick or rebase sequence it might be able to take advantage
4928   * of the cached_pairs in that next merge.
4929   */
4930  opt->priv->renames.merge_trees[0] = merge_base;
4931  opt->priv->renames.merge_trees[1] = side1;
4932  opt->priv->renames.merge_trees[2] = side2;
4933  trace2_region_leave("merge", "merge_start", opt->repo);
4934
4935  merge_ort_nonrecursive_internal(opt, merge_base, side1, side2, result);
4936  trace2_region_leave("merge", "incore_nonrecursive", opt->repo);
4937}
4938
4939void merge_incore_recursive(struct merge_options *opt,
4940          struct commit_list *merge_bases,
4941          struct commit *side1,
4942          struct commit *side2,
4943          struct merge_result *result)
4944{
4945  trace2_region_enter("merge", "incore_recursive", opt->repo);
4946
4947  /* We set the ancestor label based on the merge_bases */
4948  assert(opt->ancestor == NULL);
4949
4950  trace2_region_enter("merge", "merge_start", opt->repo);
4951  merge_start(opt, result);
4952  trace2_region_leave("merge", "merge_start", opt->repo);
4953
4954  merge_ort_internal(opt, merge_bases, side1, side2, result);
4955  trace2_region_leave("merge", "incore_recursive", opt->repo);
4956}
